        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 12:28PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 1228 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Toledo to Lawson. Movement was east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cornerville...                    Florence...
Johnsonville...                   Wilmar...
Pigeon Hill...                    Morgan Point Recreation Area...
McGehee...                        Reed...
Relfs Bluff...                    Weeks...
Monticello...                     Blanchton...
Fresno...                         McArthur...
Valley...                         Pansy...
Rock Springs...                   Mt Zion...
Avery...                          Winchester...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for southeastern
and southwestern Arkansas.</instruction>
